{"key":"processedPost-15628928","value":{"id":15628928,"first":15627879,"last":15629294,"when":1325943978,"utime":"01/07/12 03:46 PM","content":"I'm disappointed people kept answering what it means to 'simmer' as if you were cooking spaghetti sauce.<br /><br />You don't simmer with pf tek.&nbsp; You're supposed to BOIL, because it's the steam which sterilizes, not the hot water.&nbsp; Your jars should be elevated out of the water, and the steam is what does the work.<br /><br />You're supposed to leave the stove on high until steam escapes from your tight fitting lid on the pot.&nbsp; Then, you reduce the stove to the lowest setting which will keep steam escaping, which means the water will still be in a rapid boil during the whole process.&nbsp; You'll just have to experiment to find that setting, but if no steam is escaping from under the lid, no sterilization is taking place.<br /><br />Add water if necessary during the process to prevent the pot boiling dry.&nbsp; It helps to have a second pot of water boiling, so you can pour already hot water in if needed.<br /><br />I suggest you watch all four <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/BRF-Pf-Tek\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">brf tek videos</a> before proceeding further.&nbsp; They demonstrate the whole process.<br />RR","title":"Re: What Counts As A Simmer?.. [Sterilizing]","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}